column1: Maharaja Sayajirao University of Baroda, Vadodara
info: Maharaja Sayajirao University of Baroda was established by Sir Pratapsinghrao Gaekwad in the year 1949. Maharaja Sayajirao University of Baroda Vadodara was earlier known as Baroda College which came into existence in the year 1881. The University imparts education to more than 35,000 students and has a strength of more than 1200 faculty members and 1500 administrative staff. The University is approved by the University Grants Commission (UGC). MSU offers undergraduate, postgraduate, diploma and doctoral programmes related to several disciplines. The University also offers admissions to programmes based on the scores of the entrance test and aptitude test conducted by them.

info: Loyola College is a catholic minority institution which was established in 1925 which was formed with the objective of imparting education to students in a Christian environment. Loyola College is affiliated to the University of Madras. The college received recognition from the Scientific and Industrial Research Organisation in 2010 by the Department of Scientific and Industrial Research, Government of India. The institute offers UG, PG and doctoral programmes related to various disciplines. The institute offers admission to UG programmes based on the interview conducted by the authority while admission to PG programmes is done through an entrance test and admission to doctoral programmes are done through a written test followed by an interview.

info: Chandigarh University (CU), Chandigarh was established in the year 2012 by the Punjab State Legislature. The University is recognised by the University Grants Commission (UGC). info: Jaipur National University, Jaipur (JNU Jaipur) is a private self-financed University which is sponsored by Mahima Shiksha Samiti. There are 17 schools which come under the umbrella of the University: School of Business and Management, School of Engineering & Technology, School of Computer & Systems Sciences, School of Education, School of Hotel Management & Catering Technology, School of Languages, Literature & Society, School of Social Sciences, School Of Distance Education & Learning, School of Life & Basic Sciences, School of Pharmaceutical Sciences, School of Media Studies, School of Fashion Design, School of Law & Governance, School of Nursing, School of Allied Health Sciences, School of Agriculture Sciences and Institute for Medical Sciences and Research Centre. JNU Jaipur offers B.Tech, MBBS, BBA, MCA, B.Ed., B.Pharma, BHMCT, MBA, B.Sc.+B.Ed., BA, BA+BEd, BFD, MEd, M.Pharma, M.Tech, Diploma, B.Com, B.Pharma+MBA, BSc, BSc+MSc, B.Tech+MBA, BA & MA, BCA, BHMCT+MBA, BJMC, BPT, BPT+MBA, BPT+MPT, D.Pharma, DMLT, LLB, LLM, M.Phil, MSc+MBA, MSc, MA+M.Phil, MA & PhD, MA, MJMC, MPT, PG Diploma, Pharma D. and PhD programmes.

info: Uttaranchal University, DehradunÂ was established under the Uttaranchal University Act, 2012 in the year 2013. info: The Haridev Joshi University of Journalism and Mass Communication (HJUJ) is a state university established in 1996 through an Act of the Rajasthan Vidhan Sabha. HJUJ is named after an eminent former Chief Minister of Rajasthan, Haridev Joshi, who was also a freedom fighter and a committed journalist in the tribal region of Banswara. HJUJâs curriculum offers a combine theory and practices through its academic programmes, which are based on an interdisciplinary approach. This is a professional university dedicated to media academics. The courses offered at HJU provide a healthy mix of theoretical knowledge, technical skills and practical training in the various specialized areas of journalism and mass communication. HJUJ is recognised by UGC and approved by AICTE, Pharmacy Council and also approved by Bar Council.

column1: Dr Shyama Prasad Mukherjee University, Ranchi
info: Dr Shyama Prasad Mukherjee University, Ranchi was established as a Government Intermediate College in the year 1926 during the Pre- Independent India. The university is also known as DSPMU. DSPMU courses include a number of traditional and vocational/self-financing courses that are offered at the UG and PG level.

info: Sardar Patel University, Balaghat was established under the Government of Madhya Pradesh. The university is approved by the University Grants Commission (UGC), All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE), Bar Council of India (BCI), Pharmacy Council of India (PCI), National Council for Teacher Education (NCTE) and Indian Council of Agricultural Research (ICAR). SPU Balaghat lies over an area of 80 acres providing various academic and infrastructural facilities to the students faculty members of the university including library, transportation, hostels, health centre and counselling services. column1: Mahatma Jyoti Rao Phoole University, Jaipur
info: Mahatma Jyoti Rao Phoole University was established in the year 2009 under Act 3 of 2009 by legislative of the state of Rajasthan as per section 2F of the UGC Act, 1956. The university is also known as MJRP and it is the first private university of Rajasthan to be recognised by the Department of Scientific & Industrial Research (DSIR) as Scientific Industrial Research Organization (SIROs). MJRP courses are offered in the field of Bio-Technology/Biotech, Ph. D., PG UG Programmes, M. Sc. Agriculture Science & Technology, B. Sc. Honors Agriculture, MBA Agribusiness, Pharmacy, LLB, LLM, B. Tech. and Fashion Designing. Mahatma Jyoti Rao Phoole University is approved by the Bar Council of India (BCI), Pharmacy Council of India (PCI), University Grants Commission (UGC) and National Council for Teacher Education. Students wanting to know more about MJRPU can read the further part of the article.

info: Mewar University, Chittorgarh was established under the Government of Rajasthan. The college is managed by the Mewar Education Society (MES). It is recognised by the University Grants Commission (UGC), All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE), Pharmacy Council of India (PCI) and Bar Council of India (BCI). The university manages various institutes namely Mewar Institute of Management, Mewar Law Institute, Mewar Girls Business School, Mewar Girls College, Mewar Girls Ayurved Nursing Centre, Mewar Girls Industrial Training Centre, Mewar Girls College of Teachers Training etc. The university also provides various academic and infrastructural facilities to the students and faculty members of the institute including hostels, canteen, health centre, central library, auditorium, guest house, workshops, laboratories, transportation, sports, gymnasium etc.

info: Khallikote University Berhampur was established in the year 2015 by Government of Odisha and recognised by the University Grant Commission (UGC). The university is also known as KUB. info: Rashtrasant Tukadoji Maharaj (RTM) Nagpur University is the oldest University in central India and has celebrated its 100th Convocation in 2014. The university is popularly known asÂ Nagpur University.Â This is a State University governed by Maharashtra Public Universities Act, 2016. Presently University comprises Forty-Four Postgraduate Teaching Departments (PGTD). The university offers research programs in thirty-nine departments and three conducted colleges which are propelled through M.Phil., Ph.D. and Post-Doctorate programmes. The total programmes offered by the university are 891. Â All of these programmes are UGC approved. The Departments and conducted college/Institution buildings are spread over in 11 campuses with an overall area of 318 acres.Â

info: Sri Padmavati Mahila Visvavidyalayam (SPMVV), Tirupati was established under the Sri Padmavati Mahila Visvavidyalayam Act of 1983 in 1983 by Sri N.T.Rama Rao, the then Chief Minister of Andhra Pradesh. info: K.R. Mangalam University, Gurgaon was established under the Haryana Private Universities Act in the year 2013. The university is also known as KRMU. The university spreads over 26 acres of land. KRMU is recognised by the University Grants Commission under section 2f of the UGC Act, 1956. The university is approved by the Haryana Government, Council of Architecture (COA), Pharmacy Council of India (PCI), National Council for Teacher Education (NCTE), Bar Council of India (BCI) and it is a member of the Association of Indian Universities (AIU) and Association of Common Wealth Universities (ACU). KRMU offers various courses at the undergraduate, postgraduate and doctoral level through its School of Architecture & Planning, School of Engineering & Technology, School of Humanities, School of Education, School of Basic & Applied Sciences, School of Journalism & Mass Communication, School of Hotel Management & Catering Technology, School of Medical & Allied Sciences, School of Fashion, School of Agricultural Sciences, School of Management & Commerce and School of Legal Studies.Â

column1: Guru Gobind Singh Indraprastha University, Delhi
info: Guru Gobind Singh Indraprastha University (GGSIPU)Â is a teaching and affiliating University which was formerly known as Indraprastha University. This university was established in the year 1998 by the government of NCT of Delhi and it is recognised by the University Grants Commission (UGC). The university is popular by the name of IP University. It offers undergraduate and postgraduate courses in engineering, technology, management studies, medicine, pharmacy, nursing, education, and law, etc through its various schools and affiliated institutions (government and self-financed). The admission to these courses is either through national level tests conducted by various designated agencies accepted by the University or through common entrance tests (CET) conducted by the University.

column1: Centurion University of Technology and Management, Bhubaneswar
info: Centurion University of Technology and Management, Bhubaneswar was established in August 2010. It was earlier called Jagannath Institute for Technology and Management (JITM) which was established in the year 2005. The University is approved by the University Grants Commission (UGC) and All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE). Centurion University of Technology and Management, Bhubaneswar provides undergraduate, postgraduate, diploma and doctoral programmes related to various disciplines. The University also conducts an entrance test of their own called Centurion University Entrance Examination (CUEE) to offer admission to B.Tech and B.E students. About 3265 students were admitted to various programmes including UG, PG, Diploma and Ph.D during the year 2019, out of which 46 international students were also included.

info: GD Goenka University, Gurgaon was established by the GD Goenka Group in the year 2013 through the Haryana Private Universities (Amendment) Act, 2013. The institute is also known as GDGU. G.D.Goenka University is approved by University Grants Commission (UGC) under section 22 of University Grants Commission Act, 1956. All the laws programmes offered by GDGU are approved by Bar Council of India (BCI) whereas architecture programmes are approved by Council of Architecture (CoA). All the education programmes of GDGU are recognised by the National Council of Teachers Education (NCTE). Pharmacy Council of India has approved all the pharmacy courses of GD Goenka University, Gurgaon. GDGU is approved by All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE), Ministry of Human Resource Development, Government of India, New Delhi. GD Goenka University, Gurgaon is a member of Association of Indian Universities (AIU), International Association of Universities (IAU) and Association of Commonwealth Universities (ACU). All the diploma, undergraduate, postgraduate and P.hD programmes are offered through the School of Architecture & Planning, School of Communication, School of Engineering, School of Fashion & Design, School of Hospitality, School of Humanities & Social Science, School of Law, School of Management, School of Education, School of Medical and Allied Sciences, School of Agriculture and School of Basic and Applied Sciences.Â

info: Aligarh Muslim University (AMU) is a public university, which occupies a prominent position amongst universities and institutions of higher learning in the country. The University is recognised by UGC and is a member of AUI. AMU evolved out of the Mohammedan Anglo-Oriental College (MAO College) in 1920. Mohammedan Anglo-Oriental College was set up in 1877 by the great visionary and social reformer, Sir Syed Ahmad khan and with the objective to disseminate knowledge and to provide the necessary skills and mental attitude to face the vagaries of life. AMU is situated at Aligarh and has the campus, which is spread over 467 hectares. AMU offers conventional as well as vocational undergraduate, and postgraduate courses. The courses are offered under the 12 faculties, which include social sciences, sciences, humanities, technical, vocational and interdisciplinary studies. Through these faculties, AMU offers 300 courses in the traditional and modern branches of education. Students from all over the states in India and from different countries, especially Africa, West Asia and Southeast Asia join the various programmes offered by the AMU. The special feature of the University is its residential character as most of the staff and students are residing on the campus.Â

info: Pondicherry University, Puducherry (PU) is a Central University established by an Act of Parliament on 16th October 1985. 95 colleges are affiliated to PU. info: Sam Higginbottom Institute of Agriculture Technology and Science, Allahabad was established in 1991 under Â the Ecumenical Minority Christian Society namely the Sam Higginbottom Educational and Charitable Society. The foundation stone of SHUATS was laid by Dr. Sam Higginbottom. The Institute received the status of a deemed to be University on 15th March, 2000. The Institute is recognised by the University Grants Commission (UGC). The University offers admissions to students on forty-two undergraduate programmes, hundred and one postgraduate programmes, sixteen diploma programmes and doctoral programme related to various disciplines. The University is also recognised by the Association of Indian Universities (AIU), Indian Agricultural Universities Association (IAUA), International Association of Universities (IAU), All India Association for Christian Higher Education (AIACHE), Association of Commonwealth Universities, Asia-Pacific Association of Agricultural Research Institutions (APAARI), Global Consortium of Higher Education and Research for Agriculture (GCHERA).

info: Karnataka Janapada Vishwavidyalaya is the first folklore university in the world. It was established by the state government of Karnataka with the objective to provide the greater platform to Folklore Studies and to develop Kannada folkloristics on scientific principles. The various programmes offered by the university provide higher education and research in all the subjects of folklore, literature, art, music, theatre, handicrafts, folk medicine, food, beverage, and cottage industries of Karnataka. These programmes offered by University strengthen the indigenous culture to face the challenges of globalization effectively. At present this is the only university in Asia that provides advanced teaching, learning, and research opportunities to students of folklore. Karnataka Janapada Vishwavidyalaya is also known as Karnataka Folklore University, established in 2011 by an act of Karnataka Janapada Vishwavidyalaya Adhiniyama 2011. The University is recognized by UGC, AICTE, NCTE, and PCI. The university offers various postgraduate, diploma and certificate level programmes. It also offers integrated, M.Phil and PhD programmes, which connect folklore with science, management, art and medicine. Further reading of the article offers you various glimpses of the University, which include admission process, facilities, and other important details, which will help you to get acquainted with the University before sending your application to it.

info: Mother Teresa Womenâs University was established by the enactment of Tamil Nadu Act 15 in the year 1984. The university is also known as MTWU. info: Adamas University, KolkataÂ was established in 2014. The university is managed by the Sachis Kiran Roy Memorial Trust (SKRMT). info: Atal Bihari Vajpayee Hindi VishwavidyalayaÂ was established in 2011, to promote Hindi medium in all the academic faculties. Till now the Vishwavidyalaya has developed 231 academic programmes in Â Hindi for 18 faculties. Candidates of the VIshwavidyalaya, have to study the Hindi language along with one foreign language and one regional language. The University offers these courses through the regular and correspondence mode.

column1: State University of Performing and Visual Arts, Rohtak
info: Pandit Lakhmi Chand State University of Performing and Visual Arts, Rohtak was established through Haryana Act No. 24 of 2014 on August 5, 2014. The university is also known as State University of Performing and Visual Arts, Rohtak and PLCSUPVA. The university has been established integrating four Government Technical Institutions - State Institute of Fine Arts (SIFA), State Institute of Film & Television (SIFT), State Institute of Design (SID) and State Institute of Urban Planning & Architecture (SIUPA). PLCSUPVA offers undergraduate and postgraduate courses to the students in the field of Fine Arts, Design, Film & Television and Architecture. info: Panjab University Chandigarh was established in the year 1882. The University was initially started in Lahore but now got shifted to Chandigarh in 1965-1960. The University lies over an area of 550 acres. PUCHD is recognised by the University Grants Commission (UGC). The University of Punjab Chandigarh is affiliated to 188 colleges all over Punjab and 6 constituent colleges located at Sikhwala (Sri Muktsar Sahib), Balachaur (SBS Nagar), Nihal Singh Wala (Moga), Dharamkot (Moga), Mohkam Khan Wala (Ferozepur) and Guru Har Sahai (Ferozepur). The University provides a number of undergraduate, postgraduate, diploma and doctoral programmes related to various disciplines. The University offers admissions to its various programmes through different University level entrance exams namely Panjab University Tourism & Hospitality Aptitude Test (PUTHAT), Panjab University Undergraduate Common Entrance Test (PU-CET UG), Panjab University Postgraduate Common Entrance Test (PU-CET PG), PU - M.PHIL. & Ph.D etc.

info: University of Rajasthan, JaipurÂ was established in the year 1947. The university is also known as UNIRAJ. UNIRAJ was formerly known as the University of Rajputana later on in the year 1957 after the merger of Ajmer-Merwara with the State of Rajasthan it was named to University of Rajasthan. The university was temporarily functioning in the Kesargarh Fort. Shri C. Rajagopalachari laid the foundation stone of the University Campus at Jawahar Lal Nehru Marg. UNIRAJ is recognised by University Grants Commission under sections2fand 12BofUGCAct. University of Rajasthan, Jaipur spreads over 338.14 acres of land. UNIRAJ has around 9 Faculties, 37 Departments and18 Research Centres. The nine faculties of UNIRAJ are- Arts, Commerce, Education, Engineering & Technology, Fine Arts, Law, Management, Science and Social Science. University of Rajasthan, Jaipur has been recognised as University with Potential for Excellence (UPE) by University Grants Commission. UNIRAJ offers UG, PG, M. Phil. Ph.D., Certificate, PG Diploma and Diploma courses to the students.

column1: Centurion University of Technology and Management, Paralakhemundi
info: Centurion University was established in August 2010. It was earlier called Jagannath Institute for Technology and Management (JITM) which was established in the year 2005. The University is approved by the University Grants Commission (UGC) and All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE). Centurion University Paralakhemundi provides undergraduate, postgraduate, diploma and doctoral programmes related to various disciplines. The University also conducts an entrance test of their own called Centurion University Entrance Examination (CUEE) to offer admission to B.Tech and B.E students. About 3265 students were admitted to various programmes including UG, PG, Diploma and Ph.D during the year 2019, out of which 46 international students were also included.

info: Jagannath University, Jaipur is a private university, established by Rajasthan State Legislature in 2008. Jagannath University, Jaipur offers undergraduate, postgraduate and PhD courses in engineering and technology, architecture, commerce and management, science, education, vocational, paramedical and allied health, physiotherapy and pharmacy. Â The admissions to these courses are offered through the various modes which include, entrance exam conducted by Jagannath University, which is known as Jagannath University Entrance Exam (JUEE), qualifying examinations and national level entrance examinations.

column1: Veer Bahadur Singh Purvanchal University, Jaunpur
info: Veer Bahadur Singh Purvanchal University, Jaunpur was established as an affiliating university under U.P. state university act 1973 on October 2, 1987. The university was formerly known as Purvanchal University, Jaunpur. The university is also known as VBSPU. Veer Bahadur Singh Purvanchal University, Jaunpur is the result of the hard work of Â Late. Veer Bahadur Singh, then Chief Minister of Uttar Pradesh, through Gazette number 5005/15-10-87-15 (15)-86 T. C. dated September 28, 1987. A total of 559 colleges are affiliated to VBSPU. Veer Bahadur Singh Purvanchal University, Jaunpur is approved by the All India Council for Technical Education, Ministry of Human Resource Development, Government of India, New Delhi and is recognised by the University Grants Commission. Science, Applied Social Science, Medicine, Management, Engineering and Technology, Applied Physics, Chemistry, Mathematics and Humanities are the teaching faculties that have 18 departments under it that offer VBSPU courses.Â

info: Christ University, Bangalore (CU) was established in 1969 as Christ College. The University Grants Commission (UGC) of India conferred Autonomy to Christ College in 2004. Christ University courses include Arts and Humanities, Social Sciences, Sciences, Commerce, Management, Business Studies and Social Sciences, Engineering, Law and Architecture. column1: SRM Institute of Science and Technology, Chennai
info: SRM Institute of Science and Technology (SRMIST) is a deemed university, formerly known as SRM University is located in Kattankulathur, Kanchipuram, near Chennai. It was founded in 1985 as SRM Engineering College in Kattankulathur, under the University of Madras. SRMIST campuses are present at Kattankulathur, Ramapuram, Vadapalani Campus â all in and around Chennai and Modinagar, NCR, Delhi. The university is recognised by the University Grants Commission. Â SRMIST courses are offered at the undergraduate, postgraduate and doctoral level in Engineering, Management, Medicine and Health Sciences, and Science and Humanities. Candidates desirous to know more about SRMIST can read the article further and get an insight into the accreditation, location, club, etc.

column1: Sathyabama Institute of Science and Technology, Chennai
info: Sathyabama Institute of Science and Technology (Deemed to be University) was established in 1987 by Dr. Jeppiaar. The institution was formerly known as Sathyabama Engineering College. However, later it was renamed as Sathyabama Institute of Science and Technology. The college offers courses in disciplines like engineering, science, technology and education. Some of the courses offered include BE, B.Tech, B.Des, B.Arch, BSc., BBA, BA, B.Com, D.Pharma, Nursing, MA, MSc., M.Tech, MBA, etc. The institute offers admission to undergraduate programmes through an institute level entrance exam - Sathyabama All India Entrance Examination (SAEEE), while admission to PG programmes is offered based on the scores in the qualifying examinations.

info: Kumaun University, Nainital was established in the year 1973 by notification No. (10)/8651/15/75(85)/64 dated 23 November 1973 under the Act No. 10 of State Legislature. The university was the result of the merger of two Government Colleges, D.S.B. Government P.G.College, Nainital and Almora Government P.G. College, Almora. The university is recognised by the University Grants Commission, New Delhi under section 12-B of the UGC Act, 1956. DSB Campus, Nainital, SSJ Campus, Almora and Sir JC Bose Technical Campus, Bhimtal are the campuses of the varsity. Kumaun University offers a variety of courses at the undergraduate, postgraduate and doctoral level.

info: Baba Mastnath University, Rohtak was established in 2012 under the Government of Haryana. The university is managed by Shri Baba Mastnath Math, Asthal Bohar. The university is recognised by the University Grants Commission (UGC). Baba Mastnath University, Rohtak offers admissions to various undergraduate, postgraduate and doctoral programmes related to various disciplines including Ayurveda, Physiotherapy, Nursing, Sciences, Pharmacy, Humanities, Management & Commerce, Law, Naturopathy & Yogic Sciences, Engineering, Education, Mass Media, Computer Sciences, Languages like Hindi, Sanskrit and English, Social Work, Medical and Para-Medical, Pharmacy, Life and Basic Sciences. The university lies over an area of 200 acres providing various academic and infrastructural facilities to the students and faculty including administrative blocks, library, hostels, auditorium, conference halls, labs, sports, transport etc.

column1: Central University of Tamil Nadu, Thiruvarur
info: Central University of Tamil Nadu (CUTN), ThiruvarurÂ was established in the year 2009 by an Act of Parliament. The University was founded by the Government of India. The Government of Tamil Nadu allotted 516.76 acres of land in two revenue villages named Neelakudi and Nagakudi. The academic campus of CUTN is spread over 412.06 acres of land in Neelakudi Village and the residential campus spreads over 104.73 acres in Nagakudi Village. CUTN is recognised by the University Grants Commission (UGC). The University offers undergraduate (BPA, B.Sc), integrated (MBA, M.Sc, B.Sc B.Ed), postgraduate (M.Lib.I.Sc, MBA, M.Com, MA, M.Tech, M.Sc, MSW, PGD, LLM) and research (M.Phil, Ph.D) courses in various areas.Â

column1: Dakshina Bharat Hindi Prachar Sabha Chennai
info: Dakshina Bharat Hindi Prachar Sabha Chennai was established in 1918 by Mahatma Gandhi under the Ministry of Human Resource Development, Government of India. The foundation stone of the college was laid by Janab Abdul Hameed Khan and the college building was inaugurated by Pandit Jawaharlal Nehru, former President of India. The Institute is spread over an area of 7 acres. Dakshina Bharat Hindi Prachar Sabha offers admission to programmes like B.Ed, M.Ed, M.Phil Hindi, MA Hindi, PGD Journalism, Ph.D Hindi, Post Graduate Diploma in Translation etc.

column1: Indian Institute of Information Technology Design and Manufacturing Kancheepuram
info: Indian Institute of Information Technology Design and Manufacturing Kancheepuram was established by the Ministry of Human Resource Development, Government of India in the year 2007. The institution is also known as IIITDM Kancheepuram. Earlier the institute was functioning in its temporary campus at Indian Institute of Technology Madras and later on in the year 2011, it started functioning in its permanent campus at Kelambakkam-Vandalur road near Chennai. IIITDM Kancheepuram is an institute of national importance and is a Centre of Excellence for technical education and research. Indian Institute of Information Technology Design and Manufacturing Kancheepuram offers doctoral programmes, M.Des in Mechanical Systems Design, Electronic Systems Design, Communication Systems Design, Â 5 Dual Degree Programmes leading to B.Tech and M.Tech Degrees and B.Tech programmes in Computer Engineering, Electronics and Communication Engineering (Design & Manufacturing) and Mechanical Engineering (Design & Manufacturing).Â

info: Parul University is a private university established by the state government of Gujarat in 2015 under Gujarat Private Universities Act. info: Jain University Bangalore was established in 1990. The University was initially started as Sri Bhagawan Mahaveer Jain College. JU Bangalore was declared Deemed to be University in 2008. The University is recognised by the University Grants Commission (UGC). There are more than 13, 530 students seeking education under Jain University and about 545 teaching staff imparting education to students. The University also conducts an entrance examination of its own called as the Jain Entrance Test (JET) to offer admissions to certain programmes. The University offers admissions to B.E/B.Tech, B.Des, M.E/M.Tech, M.Com, M.Des, MBA, Ph.D, M.Phil, LL.M, B.A, B.Com, BBA, BCA, B.Sc, BMS, M.Sc, M.Com, M.A, MCA programmes related to various subjects. Jain University, Bangalore also offers a variety of infrastructural and academic facilities to the students and faculty members of the University.

info: Manipur University (MU) is a teaching-cum-affiliating university established in 1980 under the Manipur University Act. The University is a state university and it was converted into a central university since 2005. At present, the University has 48 affiliated colleges which include two medical colleges. Manipur Institute of Technology (MIT) is a constituent college of the University. The University offers undergraduate, postgraduate and PhD courses through its various schools, which include School of Humanities, School of Human and Environmental Science, School of Life Sciences, School of Mathematical and Physical Sciences, School of Engineering and School of Medical Sciences.

column1: IK Gujral Punjab Technical University, Jalandhar
info: I.K Gujral Punjab Technical University (IKGPTU), Jalandhar was established in 1997 under the Punjab Technical University Act, 1996 (Punjab Act No.1 of 1997). The campus spreads over 78.16 acres of land. IKGPTU is approved by the All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE) and University Grants Commission (UGC). Currently, I.K Gujral Punjab Technical University offers Undergraduate courses (B.Tech, B.Sc, BBA, BA Journalism and Mass Communication, BCA, B.Arch), Postgraduate courses (M.Tech, MCA, M.Sc, M.Arch, M.Arch, MBA, M.Com) and Doctoral (Ph.D.) courses to the students.

info: Rabindra Bharati University (RBU), Kolkata was established under the Rabindra Bharati Act on May 8, 1962. The campus spreads over 17 acres of land. column1: English and Foreign Languages University, Hyderabad
info: The English and Foreign Languages University was formerly known as the Central Institute of English and Foreign Languages. EFL University has three campuses. The main campus is in Hyderabad, while the other two are in Lucknow and Shillong. It was established on 3 August 2007 by an Act of Parliament. The university has 7 Schools and 26 Departments. It taught 11 foreign languages apart from other humanities courses through various programmes. It offers 10 undergraduate courses of three-years duration and 18 postgraduate courses of two-year duration. The University also offers 20 diploma programmes annually. The research programmes are offered by all the schools.Â

info: Jawaharlal Nehru Technological University College of Engineering HyderabadÂ was established by the Government of Andhra Pradesh in the year 1965. The institute is also known as JNTUHCEH. The institute is formerly known as Nagarjuna Sagar Engineering College. JNTUHCEH is affiliated to Osmania University, Hyderabad and is administrated under the control of the Department of Technical Education. After the establishment of Jawaharlal Nehru Technological University (JNTU) in the year 1972, it was made as a constituent college of Jawaharlal Nehru Technological University and was renamed to JNTU College of Engineering, Hyderabad. info: Indian Institute of Social Welfare and Business Management, Kolkata (IISWBM) is a B-School which was established on 25th April 1953 by a resolution passed by the Senate of the University of Calcutta. info: Marian College Kuttikkanam (Marian College) was established in the year 1995. The campus is spread over 27 acres of land. The College is approved and granted by the All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE) and the University Grants Commission (UGC). Marian College is affiliated to Mahatma Gandhi University Kottayam.

info: Andhra Loyola College was established in 1953 and it is managed and administered by the members of the Society of Jesus (Jesuits). The college offers Intermediate (+2), Degree, and Postgraduate courses and conducts research programmes in collaboration with several reputable universities. Focusing its excellent contribution to the cause of higher education, in 1988 the college was accorded the status of autonomy for the degree-level programmes by the University Grants Commission (UGC). The College is affiliated to the Krishna University and the UG and PG degree are conferred by the University. The College is recognised as the College With Potential For Excellence. This scheme was introduced by the University Grants Commission (UGC) which encourages selected Universities to reach world-class standards in their chosen domain(s) and provide additional funds to them to reach the target. The article further shares with you the detailed admission process, facilities provided by the institution and other details like ranking and accreditation, which can influence your decision to take admission at Andhra Loyola College.

column1: Guru Nanak Khalsa College of Arts, Science and Commerce, Mumbai
info: Guru Nanak Khalsa College of Arts, Science and Commerce was established in the year 1937 and the institute was the brainchild of Dr. B. R. Ambedkar. The institute was also known as Guru Nanak Khalsa College or Khalsa College Mumbai. The university is recognised by the University Grants Commission under section 2f in 1974 and UGC has also awarded the college with Potential for Excellence. Guru Nanak Khalsa College is also recognised by the Scientific and Industrial Research Organisation (SIRO). Guru Nanak Khalsa College of Arts, Science and Commerce is affiliated to the University of Mumbai. The college offers various courses at the UG, PG and doctoral level along with admitting students in class 11.

column1: Dev Samaj College for Women, Ferozepur
info: The Dev Samaj College for Women (DSCW) is located in the city of Ferozepur in Punjab. This city lies near the border with Pakistan, on the banks of the river Satluj. As the name suggests, the college is meant exclusively for the education of women. The college is named after Shri Bhagwan Dev Atma, who was a spiritual and religious guru. The DSCW is affiliated to the Panjab University in Chandigarh. This affiliation, ensures approval with the UGC (University Grants Commission). In addition, the DSCW has also been accredited by the NAAC (National Assessments and Accreditation Council). A separate IQAC (Internal Quality Assurance Cell) has been created to this end, to ensure that all the terms of the NAAC are complied with. An AQAR (Annual Quality Assurance Report) gets generated to quantify the results. The campus is spread over 25 acres of land.Â

info: Womenâs Christian College was founded on 7th July 1915 as a joint venture of 12 missionary societies from the UK, USA, and Canada, under the able leadership of the first Principal, Dr. Miss Eleanor McDougall, with 41 students and 7 faculty in Â Hyde Park, rented premises in Kilpauk. Â  Declared a first grade college in 1916, WCC purchased the imposing Doveton House built circa 1798 and set Â within 11 acres of sylvan surroundings along the banks of the River Cooum in Nungambakkam, using a gift of $25,000, generously donated by the Womenâs American Baptist Fellowship Missionary Society from the legacy of Mrs. Laura Spelman Rockefeller. Â The College shifted to its new home on College Road on 5 July 1916 and as the number of students grew, bought up 2 adjacent parcels of land and buildings bringing up the total acreage to 20.

info: New Alipore College, Kolkata was established as a Government Sponsored College on August 5, 1963. Earlier there were only six departments namely English, History, Bengali, Sanskrit, Philosophy and Mathematics were functioning. Later on in the year 1965, Chemistry, Physics, Economics and Political Science departments were added. The college is affiliated to the University of Calcutta. The institute governed by the Government of West Bengal. New Alipore College, Kolkata offers undergraduate and postgraduate courses to the students in the field of arts, science and commerce.

column1: Dr Gafoor Memorial MES Mampad College, Malappuram
info: The Dr. Gafoor Memorial MES Mampad College is located in the town of Mampad, which lies in the Malappuram district of Kerala. The college was founded in the year 1965. The college campus covers a total area worth twenty- seven acres of land. As the name suggests, this college has been named in memory of Dr. P.K. Abdul Gafoor, who was the founding president of the MES (Muslim Educational Society). He was also an eminent educator in his time. His society the MES had gone on to become the highest disseminator of scholarships in the country then. This college is also an associated of the Delhi- based Foundation for Academic Excellence and Access (FAEA).

info: St Thomas College Thrissur was established in 1919. The foundation stone of the College was laid in 1889 by then Vicar Apostolic of Thrissur, Rt. Rev. Adolphus Edwin Medlycott. The College initially started functioning as a high school but later got the status of Autonomous College in the University of Calicut in 2014The college was affiliated to the University of Kerala in 1957 and to the University of Calicut in 1968. STC Thrissur has currently 23 departments, 14 PG programmes, 23 UG programmes. The Institute currently has a total capacity of 2752 students, 147 teachers, 23 research supervisors and 53 research students in 8 research centres. STC Thrissur lies with an area of 28.87 acres comprising the Administrative Block, Academic Block, Jubilee Block for self financing programmes, the Sports Complex and the Centenary Campus with an area of 16567 sq m. The Institute is recognised by the University Grants Commission (UGC).

info: The First Women's College of Thrissur District, St. Mary's College, was established in the heart of the flourishing business town of Thrissur in 1946. The Congregation of Mother of Carmel (CMC) had pioneered into the field of Higher Education inspired by the educational vision of its founder, St. Kuriakose Elias Chavra. India was fast approaching the much-awaited freedom from British rule and there was great enthusiasm for a new and reformed society. Though many women had taken part in the freedom struggle, the majority of women in India were still uneducated and illiterate. Women had very little opportunity for higher education as there were very few colleges for women at the time. It is in this hour of need that the CMC congregation had established St. Maryâs College, with the aim of uplifting the women of Kerala by empowering them through education.

info: St. Joseph's College (SJC Darjeeling), Darjeeling started functioning in the year 1888 as a part of St. Joseph's School. In the year 1963, the College moved to its present location. The College was founded and is managed by Darjeeling Jesuits of North Bengal (DJNB). St. Joseph's College offers undergraduate (BA, B.Sc, B.Com, BCA, BBA) and postgraduate (MA) courses in various domains. Initially, SJC Darjeeling was affiliated to Calcutta University. From 1962, it is affiliated to the University of North Bengal.

info: Srinagar, which is the capital city of the state of Jammu and Kashmir (J & K), has a Government College for Women. This was founded back in the year 1950. As the name suggests, this one is meant only for female students. The total campus runs to a little over eight acres of land. The Government College for Women, Srinagar (GCWS) is affiliated to the University of Kashmir (KU), also located in Srinagar. This affiliation, ensures the approval by the UGC (University Grants Commission). TheÂ GCWS was earlier known as the Womenâs College Srinagar. The GCWS has been accredited by the NAAC (National Assessments and Accreditation Council), earning an A grade rating in it.Â

info: Bhim Rao Ambedkar College (BRAC), Delhi is a constituent co-educational college of the University of Delhi and it is funded by Delhi Government. It was established in 1991 to commemorate the birth centenary year of Bharat Ratna Dr. Bhim Rao Ambedkar. The college has a unique combination of academic and professional courses under the three year Bachelor Degree Programmes. The academic programmes include B.Com & B.Com (Hons.), B.A. (Hons.) Geography, B.A. (Hons.) History and Â B.A. (Programme). The college offers four professional courses which include B.A. (Hons.) Hindi Journalism and Mass Communication, B.A. (Hons.) Social Work, B.A. (Hons.) Business Economics, B.A. (Hons) Applied Psychology. The college also offers Human Resource Management (HRM), Office Management and Secretarial Practice (OMSP), and vocational course- Functional Hindi (FH).

column1: Osmania University College For Women, Hyderabad
info: Osmania University College For Women, Hyderabad was established in the year 1924. The institution is a constituent college of Osmania University. In the year 1989, the college got the autonomous status and in the year 2004, the status of College with Potential for Excellence was granted to the college by University Grants Commission. The campus is spread over 43 acres of land. Osmania University College For Women, Hyderabad offers undergraduate and postgraduate courses to the students.

column1: St Andrew's College of Arts Science and Commerce, Mumbai
info: St. Andrew's College of Arts, Science and Commerce, Mumbai was established on July 9, 1983, by the Catholic Archdiocese of Bombay (Mumbai) after getting permission from the Government of Maharashtra and the University of Mumbai. The college is also known as St. Andrew's College. The college is a Catholic minority institution and is affiliated to the University of Mumbai. St. Andrew's College of Arts, Science and Commerce, Mumbai is recognised by the University Grants Commission under sections 2(f) and 12(B). info: St Xavier's College, Kolkata (SXCCAL) was established in 1860 by the Society of Jesus, and was affiliated to Calcutta University in 1862. It was granted the status of autonomous college and college with potential for excellence by UGC in 2006, college of excellence in 2014 and college with a special heritage status in 2015. It is an ISO 9001:2015 certified institute. It has 20 UG academic departments: Commerce, Business Administration/Management, English, Bengali, Political Science, Sociology, Hindi, History, Film Studies, Journalism, Communicative English, Physics, Chemistry, Mathematics, Economics, Computer Science, Statistics, Microbiology, Mass Communication & Videography, Environmental Science. It has 9 PG departments: Commerce, Computer Science, Biotechnology, Microbiology, Physics, Multimedia & Animation, Political Science, English and Bengali. It also has a Department of Education. SXCCAL offers B.Com (Hons.), B.Ed, B.Sc (Hons.), BA, BA (Hons.), BBA (Hons.), BMS (Hons.), M.Com, M.Sc, M.Sc Integrated, MA, PG Diploma and PhD programmes.

info: St Joseph's College, Bangalore is an autonomous college which was established in 1882. The college is recognised by the University Grants Commission (UGC). SJC is affiliated to Bangalore University and follows all the rules and regulations of the university in terms of admission process. The college provides admissions to undergraduate, postgraduate and PG diploma programmes based on the merit of students in the qualifying students followed by an interview round. SJC also offers admissions to Ph.D programmes based on the merit of the written test conducted by the Bangalore University followed by an interview. The college also provides various academic and infrastructural facilities to the students and faculty members of the institute including classrooms, sports, auditorium, laboratories, hostels, library etc. SJC Bangalore has also formed many associations for the development and benefit of students.

info: Bengaluru North University (BNU), KolarÂ is trifurcated from the Bangalore University through its University Gazette Notification in 2015. As per the new Jurisdiction, the Bengaluru North University covers all the legislative assembly constituencies of Kolar district, which include Kolar P.G.Center, Chikkaballapur district, C.V.Ramannagar, K.R.Puram, Mahadevpura, Pulikeshinagar and Sarvagnanagar of Bangalore urban district and Hosakote, Devanahalli and Doddaballapur legislative constituencies of Bangalore rural districts. The college offers undergraduate and postgraduate courses in art, commerce, science and management.
